OL,3,CLabour win Avon and Somerset PCC for
OL,4,Cfirst time
OL,6,FClare Moody polled 95,982 votes,
OL,7,Ffollowed by Mark Shelford who received
OL,8,F91,006 votes. Turnout was 23.09%,
OL,9,Fcompared to 30.7% in 2021.
OL,11,FThe turnout was 23.09%, compared to
OL,12,F30.7% at the last PCC election in 2021.
OL,14,FThe force's region covers Bristol,
OL,15,FSouth Gloucestershire, North Somerset,
OL,16,FSomerset, and Bath and North East
OL,17,FSomerset.
OL,19,FPolice and Crime Commissioners were
OL,20,Ffirst introduced in 2012 as part of a
OL,21,Fwider package of police reforms.
